Similarly to an increase in life expectancy, the incidence of Parkinson's 
disease increases as well. In parallel with this, more patients with Parkinson's 
disease undergo elective or urgent surgical interventions. According to recent 
statistical data, more than half of the patients with Parkinson's disease are 
not properly managed when they are hospitalized for surgical interventions. It 
